        "short_description": "A lakeside heritage palace built during the reign of Travancore kings, reflecting Dutch, British, and Portuguese architectural styles.",
        "detailed": "Thevally Palace was constructed between 1811 and 1819. Built on the banks of Ashtamudi Lake, the palace served as an important administrative and royal guesthouse. The architecture blends Dutch, British, and traditional Kerala elements. Today, it is preserved as a cultural monument reflecting the region’s colonial-era history."
